# WhatsApp AI Fix Chunks

Workstream: CSV/Sheets import has 70+ fields but buyer AI felt hardcoded because RAG + prompts only saw ~15 DB columns.

## Chunk status

| Chunk | Scope | Flag | Status |
|-------|-------|------|--------|
| C1 | Full import field knowledge indexing + bulk per-row draftData | `FEATURE_FULL_IMPORT_KNOWLEDGE` | DONE |
| C2 | Expanded property prompt limits (amenities, description, RAG chunks) | `FEATURE_EXPANDED_PROPERTY_PROMPTS` | DONE |
| C3 | Extended attributes JSON on Property model + publish mapping | `FEATURE_EXTENDED_PROPERTY_ATTRS` | DONE |
| C4 | Staff copilot `searchPropertyKnowledge` tool | `FEATURE_COPILOT_PROPERTY_RAG` | DONE |
| C5 | Reduce fast-path bypass for property detail questions | `FEATURE_DETAIL_QUESTION_LLM` | DONE |
| C6 | Re-index all published properties script (dry-run) | `DRY_RUN=true` | DONE |
| C7 | Bulk publish knowledge gate + rollback parity | `FEATURE_BULK_PUBLISH_STRICT` | DONE |

## Safety nets (every chunk)

1. Feature flag OFF by default — instant kill switch
2. `npm run smoke` before deploy
3. `FEATURE_SHADOW_MODE=true` to log old vs new mismatches
4. Gradual rollout via `FEATURE_ROLLOUT_PERCENTAGE` where lead-scoped

## Key files

- Import→RAG: `backend/src/services/propertyKnowledge.service.ts`
- Bulk publish: `backend/src/routes/property-import-bulk.routes.ts`
- Buyer prompts: `backend/src/services/propertyAiContext.service.ts`, `ai.service.ts`
- WhatsApp More Info: `whatsappInteractiveOrchestrator.service.ts`

## Activate C1 in production

```
FEATURE_SHADOW_MODE=true          # watch logs first
FEATURE_FULL_IMPORT_KNOWLEDGE=true
```
Re-publish or re-index existing properties after enabling C1.

## Activate C2 in production

```
FEATURE_EXPANDED_PROPERTY_PROMPTS=true
```
Pairs with C1 — wider prompts only help once import fields are indexed.

## Production activation (after merge + migrate)

**Buyer-facing fixes are ON by default since 2026-06-13.** No Railway env vars required for core behavior.

On deploy, `backfillPropertyKnowledgeOnBoot` automatically re-indexes up to 200 properties with missing/sparse knowledge chunks.

Kill switches (set `=false` to disable):
- `FEATURE_FULL_IMPORT_KNOWLEDGE=false`
- `FEATURE_EXPANDED_PROPERTY_PROMPTS=false`
- `FEATURE_EXTENDED_PROPERTY_ATTRS=false`
- `PROPERTY_KNOWLEDGE_BOOT_BACKFILL=false`

Staff-only (still opt-in):
- `FEATURE_COPILOT_PROPERTY_RAG=true`
- `FEATURE_BULK_PUBLISH_STRICT=true`
